name: Discovering the Beauty of Japan's Soul

metadata.name: I’m a Shinto Samurai
metadata.description:
Sabet's exceptional artistry and love for Japan are truly remarkable. As someone who was born in Japan, I feel a deep connection to the way he beautifully weaves the country into his creations. "I'm a Shinto Samurai" serves as both a tribute to his boundless creativity and a symbol of the profound impact it has had on my life, as well as on countless others.

Artist: Sherry Mahboubian
 Mediums and Materials: Pastel and Charcoal on 10 × 10 inch Wood, Digitized 
File Type: PNG 
Dimensions: 4213 × 4235 pixels
